   /* Abigail*/
"AbigailRosalieArrivalCT": "I like Rosalie's hair ribbon! I wonder where she got it?",

"Abigail.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "Sometimes I wonder if my parents would have been better off divorced...$s #$e# I know people talk about staying for the kids, but it only hurts them more...$s",

/*Alex*/
"AlexRosalieArrivalCT": "I heard the new girl was an actress from the city. #$b# Maybe she was a plus size model? #$b# What? It's a compliment!$h",

"Alex.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "The plus size model is getting a divorce?! $u #$e# I wonder who cheated on who?$h",

/*Caroline*/
"CarolineRosalieArrivalCT": "I heard that Rosalie moved somewhere by the ocean when she and her family left. #$b# I hope Pierre doesn't start stocking sea food...$s",
/*Clint*/
"ClintOnRosalieRamp": "Don't tell Gus, but I did think that the stairs into the saloon were a bit steep.",

"ClintRosalieArrivalCT": "Rosalie and I didn't talk much as kids. I doubt that'll change. #$e# We used to hang out sometimes, but not much...",

"ClintOnRosalie": "I heard Rosalie and Emily are friends... do you think she'd put in a good word for me to Emily?",

"Clint.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "Rosalie is single?!$u #$b# Uh... I mean...$s #$b# That's too bad... Poor Rose...$s",

/*Demetrius*/
"DemetriusRosalieArrivalCT": "It's interesting how some people dress up in styles from the past. #$b# I prefer to look into the future myself.$h",
"Demetrius.RosalieGeorgeWCCT": "Have you ever seen a cat who is unable to use all their limbs? #$b# It's amazing how easily they're able to adapt. #$e# They don't know that they're any different. #$b# If only humans could be that adaptable.",

/*Dwarf*/
"DwarfRosalieArrivalCT": "I thought I heard a siren's call this morning...",

/*Elliott*/
"ElliottRosalieArrivalCT": "I heard that Miss Rosalie was an actress, but she told me she's also a writer.#$b# Leah also said she's an artist. And Gus said she's a singer. #$b# I can't imagine one person having that many passions, but it's inspiring! #$b# Then again, maybe that's what's taking a toll on the rose.$s",
"Elliott.RosalieGeorgeWCCT": "It's unfortunate that we always think of some stories as a work of fiction. #$b# I just wish Rosalie hadn't been the prom example of it.$a",

        //Added in ConversationTopicJson, but not triggered yet/
"ElliottOnRosalie": "That which we call a rose, by any other name would smell as sweet.$l #$b# Oh, I'm sorry, I've been reading the classics lately.$h",

"Elliott.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "I know Rosalie thought she found her fairytale ending,$s #$b# But the story wouldn't be as interesting if she didn't have some trials to overcome.$h #$e#I do hope she's doing alright, though...$s",

"ElliottOnRosalieRadio": "Many don't know that in the original story of 'the Little Mermaid',$s #$b# She is unable to walk on land without feeling like knives were going through her new legs.$s #$b$ Maybe there's some truth to the rumours and Miss Rosalie's condition. #$e# I certianly believe.$h",

"ElliottOnMermaidEventCT": "It's facinating when fantacy immitates reality, don't you think @?",

"Elliott.RosalieDreamsAndDisastersCT":"Shane and Rosalie's relationship make for quite the interesting story. #$b# Though I will admit, quite predictable... too predictable...$2 #$e# I hope if things are platonic, they're on the same page about that.$2 #$b# But it wouldn't make an interesting story if they were.$h",

/*
Emily
*/
"EmilyRampEventCT": "Gus left to go help his niece and left me in charge as soon as the ramp was done being installed. #$b# He seems a bit stressed, but no less excited for her to move in!$1 #$e# I don't think that Gus has taken a single day off since opening the saloon. It's sad his one day off is due to an emergency...$2",
"EmilyRosalieArrivalCT1": "Gus' niece, Rosalie, is so sweet! I think we're going to be best friends already!",
"EmilyRosalieArrivalCT2": "Huh? What? Nothing.$6 #$e# Did Haley say something?$5",
"EmilyOnRosalieWalkCT": "I feel so relaxed after going to the spa. #$b# But I wish Rosie could have joined me...$2 #$e#I hope she knows that there's nothing wrong with needing to cancel.$2 #$b#But she's so hard on herself...$2",
"Emily.RosalieGeorgeWCCT": "Rosie's been low since what happened with George.$u #$b# I hope it doesn't discourage her from going out...$s",


"Emily.RosalieDreamsAndDisastersCT1": "Shane is always looking at Rosalie to make sure she's doing okay when he's here at the saloon. #$b# It's really sweet how much he cares about his friend. #$e# I like to think that Rosie would tell me if she liked Shane in that way. Or Shane would if he did.$3",
"Emily.RosalieDreamsAndDisastersCT2": "Don't bring up Shane and Rosalie to my sister... She's not... acting like herself.$2 #$e# Why? No reason.",

/*
Evelyn
*/
"EvelynRampEventCT": "I heard that Gus had a ramp installed at the Saloon! #$b# Maybe George and I will pay a visit!$h",
"EvelynRosalieArrivalCT": "It's so nice to see Rosalie again after all this time! #$b# Now... Was she the first or second born to the nurse?",

"Evelyn.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "Back in my day, if things didn't work out between a married couple, you just stuck it out. #$e# George and I may not seem like it, but we still love each other dearly. #$b# I hope Rosalie can find that, and find peace.",

/*
George
*/
"GeorgeRosalieRamp": "So, I'm finally allowed to enter the saloon? #$b# Took 'em long enough.$5",
"GeorgeRosalieArrivalCT": "Rosalie was a thorn in my side! #$b# She always stuck sticks in my wheelchair, and disobeyed her mother! #$b# Yoba must be on my side to stick her in one, too! Heh heh!$h #$e# Wait... was she the quiet one?$s #$b# Oh... yes. She'll be fine.$h #$b# As long as she stays away from the drunk.",
"George.RosalieGeorgeWCCT": "How was I supposed to know the girl had chronic pain? #$b# She should have just said so!#$e#I know what that's like... I should probably apologize...$s#$b#...tomorrow.$h",

"George.RosaliesFlareUpEventCT": "I'm lucky that when I became disabled, Evelyn stayed with me. Made sure everything in the home was accessable.$s #$b# If Rosalie's husband couldn't do that, good riddence to him and good on her for kicking that leech to the curb.$h #$e# I'm sure that boy she was always with is dancing with joy now that the news is out$h",



